# 7. まさかのトラブル！？

Arimura: *Sigh* Technical difficulties... Missing forty minutes of footage puts us in a tough situation.
Minori: I'm surprised this kind of thing happened at a TV studio during a shoot...
Airi: Me too. I've heard of stuff like this happening, but this is my first time actually being on site as it did...
Haruka: This is the stuff of nightmares to the camera crew since such a simple mistake can cascade into fairly serious problems for the show.
Minori: I can't imagine...
Minori: (But this is really happening... What does that mean for our shoot...?)
Kuromiya: Thank you all very much for your patience! As you probably just heard, we're having some technical issues...
Kuromiya: To summarize, I'm very sorry, but we'll have to reshoot everything we just did following the break...
MYU: Yes, I had a feeling...
Haruka: Which means we'll have to do MYU's segment all over again, including trying the food.
Yuika: Oh, I'm not so sure about this now... We're going to sound really phony if we're not careful...
Minori: Y-Yeah...! We have to act like it's our first time trying them...!
Shizuku: The audience is also going to have to sit through it again...
MYU: There's something else that's worrying me...
MYU: The packaging for everything that I brought in has been opened up. How do we make them look like new?
MYU: Worse, we went through most of what we had. They're in our stomachs now.
Shizuku: Oh no...!
MYU: So, I'm not sure we can redo my segment... We might want to try shooting something else.
Minori: Something else...?!
Haruka: Right. We can't really do a segment about delectables that we don't have...
Kuromiya: Yes, I agree. I was hoping that we could come up with a solution together.
Kuromiya: However, we won't really be able to do anything that requires getting food or souvenirs from elsewhere...
Kuromiya: Which points to a talk segment. Would it be possible for you to introduce some fabulous destinations...?
Airi: Fabulous destinations...? Isn't that right up your alley, MYU?
Kuromiya: Feel free to talk about all the inns and hotels you like. We can always send some teams over to interview them at a later date.
MYU: ... Okay, I understand.
MYU: I've uploaded a lot of stuff to PicShare, so they might not seem all that new or interesting to our viewers. But I guess we don't have a choice...
Minori: (Oh...)
Minori: (Right. MYU worked really hard on this segment for the sake of everybody watching...)
Minori: (It'd be awful to see all her hard work go to waste by becoming something incomplete...)
Minori: (We don't have a choice but to change course here, but I feel like there's a better solution out there...)
Minori: (Something that more closely resembles MYU's original segment. Something that the audience will really enjoy...)
Minori: *Gasp*
Shizuku: Is something wrong, Minori?
Minori: No, uhh... I just had an idea...!
Minori: B-But it might not be a very good one since it really just popped into my head...
Haruka: Why don't you start by telling us? Your idea could very well give us the hint we need.
Kuromiya: Yes, please tell us. If your idea is better than the one I just suggested, then we'll go with that instead.
Minori: Really...?
Minori: Th-Then, okay...! So...
Minori: What if we introduced all the souvenirs that the TV station sells?
MYU: This station's souvenirs?
Arimura: The gift shop here is open to the public. Was your plan to introduce the stuff that we made on this show and the merchandise featuring this studio's mascots?
Minori: Yes! I visited just the other day and thought it was really cool how this is the only place where you can get a lot of those things.
Minori: Doing a segment on this station's gift shop seemed really fun, and they already have everything we need.
Minori: H-How does that sound...?!
MYU: ... That could actually work.
Minori: Huh...?
Yuika: I agree. I feel like that's something MYU's followers could get behind.
MYU: I'm also really interested since I don't actually know what's available in the gift shop!
MYU: So, let's go with Hanasato's idea. We can call it something like... “Check Out All The Cool Stuff In The Station's Gift Shop!”
Minori: Y-You mean it...?!
Kuromiya: Yes, we could get everything ready in no time and start a fun conversation viewers might not be expecting.
Kuromiya: Let's go with her idea... We'll just need some time to get set up.
Kuromiya: Listen, everyone! We need to be ready to shoot in thirty minutes!
TV Crew: Got it!
Minori: Oh...
Shizuku: That was amazing, Minori...! You came up with a wonderful idea in such a short amount of time!
Airi: Yeah, I wasn't sure what was gonna happen, but I think you just saved the show...
Minori: I-It really just popped into my head, but I'm glad I could help somehow!
Haruka: Anyway, all that's left is to wait for them to get the set ready.
Shizuku: Right! So until then...
Audience Member's Voice: They said they were just having some technical issues, right? What's taking them so long...?
Audience Member's Voice: Yeah, I hope they resume soon. My bottom's starting to get a little sore...
Audience Member's Voice: Including the time they took to set up, we've been sitting for like three hours now... I knew that delays were possible, but nothing this long.
Minori: Oh no...
Haruka: The audience has been waiting for quite a while now...
Airi: Yeah, and they're being asked to stay in their seats outside of breaks. Those aren't exactly what you'd call comfortable, either...
Shizuku: I hope our shoot resumes soon...
Minori: Yeah...
Minori: (Also...)
TV Crew: Excuse me, Mr. Arimura? The writer just finished making edits to the script. Would you mind taking a look with the producer?
TV Crew: Let's take this opportunity to touch up your makeup, Yuika!
TV Crew: The set's still cluttered from before, so get it ready to start again! Also, cameras, check your positions!
Minori: (The crew's scrambling to get ready, while I'm standing by doing nothing...)
Minori: (Isn't there a way for me to help...? The crew, the audience, the other guests, anything...)
Crew Member: Hey, anyone free to go buy the souvenirs MYU needs from the gift shop?!
Minori: Oh...
Minori: Yes, I'm free! I'll go buy them!
Airi: What?!
Minori: I'll be right back!
Crew Member: Hey, thanks a bunch...
Crew Member: Wait, Hanasato...?!
Haruka: Let's go with her. She's probably going to need an extra hand.
Shizuku: Oh...
Airi: She's got the right idea. We should follow her lead and also try to help.
Shizuku: I agree. Let's tell the staff what's going on and go after her.
Minori: We're back! And we've got all the gift shop's best-selling items!
MYU: Th-Thank you so much. I can't believe you actually went and got them for me.
Arimura: Wait, how much did you buy? I don't think we'll be able to get through all this.
Minori: Oh, these snacks are for the audience!
Yuika: The audience?
Minori: Yes! We thought they deserved a reward for being so patient with us...
Minori: Also, we figured it'd be more fun for them if they got to have the same things we'll be having during the segment.
MYU: You've got everything covered...
Crew Member: Thank you very much... But you really didn't have to do all this since it's technically the crew's job.
Minori: Oh, uh... I-I'm sorry for running off like that! I know we still need to redo our makeup and stuff...!
Minori: But it just didn't feel right for us to do nothing while everyone else scrambled to get things ready...
Minori: And it really didn't seem right to keep the audience waiting for so long...!
Arimura: Yes, it's important to never forget that...
Shizuku: Mr. Arimura...?
Arimura: You get into a habit of drawing lines when you're in a studio like this, but the crew and personalities all want the show they're working on to be good. We all want the audience to enjoy themselves.
Arimura: Which is why it's so important to take a step back, forget the lines in the sand and remind ourselves of what the audience is feeling.
Yuika: Yes, I agree...
MYU: I think you just taught us a valuable lesson, Hanasato. Your work ethic is beyond admirable.
Minori: What...?
Minori: N-No, I just...
Haruka: We still have some time left until we're supposed to resume, so how about we help pass these snacks out to the audience...?
Airi: Great idea! I'm sure they'll enjoy things even more if they get these from us personally.
Arimura: Yes, that would be a fun surprise.
Yuika: Alright, let's do it! I'll start from the back!
Airi: Sorry about the delay, everyone! We brought you a little treat for being so patient!
Audience Members: A treat?! For us...?!
MYU: We should be shooting again shortly, so we hope you'll enjoy these in the meantime.
Audience Members: MYU?! I can have this...?! I'm a huge fan! I follow you on PicShare...!
Shizuku: Thank goodness... The audience seems much happier now.
Haruka: Yeah, I hope this makes up for forcing them to suffer through this delay.
Minori: All that's left is to wait for the crew to finish getting everything set up.
TV Crew: Thank you all for your patience! We're ready to roll! Please take your positions!
Airi: Alright, let's get right back to it!
Minori: *Nod*
Minori: Let's do everything we can to give the audience the show they really deserve!
Airi, Shizuku & Haruka: Yeah! Yes!
